news.title: UnitedHealth Group commits to improvements after independent audit, patient backlash
news.summary: The company said it has adopted 23 ongoing "action plans" to track and implement recommended improvements. All of the plans will be completed by the end of March.

news.title: Waller had a 'strong interview' for Fed chair with Trump as president appears to turn focus to job market
news.summary: The positive description of the Waller interview by officials was not necessarily an indication that he was a favorite candidate for the job. The positive description was just part of the interview, officials said.

news.title: CNBC's Official College Sports Valuations 2025: Top 75 athletic programs
news.summary: The top 75 programs in the world are worth a combined $51.22 billion. That's 13% more than the top 75 in last year's rankings.

news.title: Wall Street banked on a flurry of deals under Trump in 2025. It wasn't that simple
news.summary: Dealmakers expected a flood of M&A to take place in 2025 following the election of President Trump. The number of transactions didn't live up to the hype.

news.title: Jeffrey Epstein files hit deadline for ordered release by DOJ on Friday
news.summary: The DOJ for months had resisted calls to released the Epstein files. The DOJ has not said why it took so long to release the files.

news.title: These are the secrets to Buffett’s investment success, according to this billionaire investor
news.summary: Seth Klarman, CEO and portfolio manager of the value-oriented investment management fund Baupost Group, says investors have much to learn from Warren Buffett.

news.title: ‘I’m not looking to leave any money to the kids’: We’re in our 60s with $1.5 million in IRAs. Can we retire next year?
news.summary: “Our current salary combined is $210,000,” he says. “We’re in a position of power. We’ve got to do something.”

news.title: Trump says affordability is a ‘hoax,’ but consumers should expect more pain in 2026
news.summary: Tariffs, an AI boom, geopolitical divisions and a new administration ushered in a unique, unsettling year for consumers. The year was also marked by a rise in the number of women in the workforce.

news.title: ‘I’m terrified I’ll be homeless when my husband, 76, stops working’: We only have $100K. What happens to people like us?
news.summary: “I’m sick of reading how many millions everyone has,” she says. “I'm sick of seeing how many billions everyone has.”

news.title: ‘I don’t know how much my wife earns’: I’m 63 with $6.4 million in stocks, mostly Apple. Will I get punished on taxes?
news.summary: “Each of our properties are worth over $1 million,” he says. “Each one of us is worth more than a million dollars.”
